PowerAPI Thrift Reporter

Creates an Apache Thrift packet and sends the power consumption using ZeroMQÂ communication channel. It allows to use the output of BitWatts in a pub/sub system.

In

Listen to ProcessedMessage, which are typically provided by fr.inria.powerapi.processor modules.

Out

Creates an Apache Thrift object and sends it using ZeroMQ as a publisher to localhost:5556. An external program listening on this port and is required (Generally a ZMQ broker to distributed the message to interested subscribers).

Configuration part

Currently no special configuration required.
